Riversdale Says in “Advanced’ Talks for Power Plant Stake Sale

-- B y   S o r a y a   P e r m a t a s a r i
-- 
2011-04-29T04:57:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/riversdale-says-in-advanced-talks-for-power-plant-stake-sale.html
Riversdale Mining Ltd. (RIV) , acquired by
Rio Tinto Group this month, is in advanced talks with a group of
potential partners for the sale of a stake in stage one of its
$1.3 billion Benga power plant project in  Africa .  The company is also in discussions to sell 220 megawatts of
power capacity from the plant in  Mozambique  to a buyer in  South
Africa , the Sydney-based company said today in a statement. The
plant is scheduled to start output in 2013. Riversdale is also
developing coal projects in Mozambique.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Soraya Permatasari in Melbourne at 
 soraya@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Hobbs at   ahobbs4@bloomberg.net  